history.content: I'd take which one interests you more. I find 164 way more interesting (but slightly higher workload) than 169A, especially if you already have an internship. Also last fall 169A feels half-baked because they were constantly changing stuff and were still figuring things out.

Hi,

I’m currently a junior (CS major) interested in SWE, and I’m having trouble deciding what course to take Fall sem of my senior year. So far, I’ve taken all required lower divs along with CS 170, CS 188, CS W186, and Data 100.

I’m planning on taking CS 161 in the fall and CS 162 in the spring. I was also planning to take CS 160 and CS 168 but it seems that they won’t be offered next year, so I’m not sure what to take instead.

Along with CS 161 for Fall, I am considering either CS 169A or CS 164 or possibly CS 194-15 (Parallel Computing), though I haven’t heard much about CS 194-15 in terms of workload/difficulty/content. I also saw a past thread that said EECS 149 is a good core class to take, though I’m not really interested in hardware so I don’t know how useful it would be for me.

I’m not very interested in compilers but I’ve heard CS 164 is good for strengthening your programming skills though it has a high workload, and I’ve also heard that if you’ve done a SWE internship (which I will be doing this summer), CS 169 is not as helpful.

Any advice/recommendations are appreciated! Thank you!
